meta {
  name: Webhook Lead Callback (Meta, Shared App)
  type: http
  seq: 8
}

post {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/meta/webhook
  body: json
  auth: none
}

headers {
  Content-Type: application/json
}

body:json {
  {
    "object": "page",
    "entry": [
      {
        "id": "123456789",
        "time": 1719100000,
        "changes": [
          {
            "field": "leadgen",
            "value": {
              "leadgen_id": "989906403816053",
              "page_id": "123456789",
              "form_id": "2217695302333588",
              "created_time": 1719100000
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}

docs {
  Same as Webhook-Post.bru, but for a Meta App shared across MULTIPLE
  tenants — the callback URL carries no integrationId.

  Requires a single ext.meta_tenant_config row with tenant_id IS NULL
  (at most one may exist — enforced by uix_meta_tenant_config_one_shared
  in db_scripts/01_init-db.sql). That row
  is not manageable through the tenant-scoped integration CRUD endpoints
  (POST/GET/PATCH /meta/integration) — insert/update it directly via SQL.

  Both tenant_id AND org_id are resolved from ext.meta_page_form_org_map
  by page_id/form_id alone (no tenant_id filter), which works because
  (page_id, form_id) is already globally unique
  (uq_meta_page_form_org_map). A matching row must exist or the lead is
  logged as "unmapped" and skipped.

  Everything else about the flow (HMAC verification against the shared
  row's app_secret, Graph API fetch using the shared row's access_token,
  field mapping, insert, pg_notify) is identical to the per-tenant path.
}
